                        ][h2]Shop Rules[/h2][
                        
                        ][br][
                        ][center]· · ─ ‧₊˚❀༉‧₊˚. ─ · ·[/center][
                        ][br][
                        
                        ][ol][
                        
                            ][li]Goes without saying: [b]all PFQ rules apply[/b] to the business done in this shop![/li][
                            
                            ][li]If you post on this shop thread, please make sure to [b]subscribe to the thread[/b]! I may forget to PM you.[/li][
                            
                            ][li][b]Do not use my templates outside of PFQ[/b]. I only makes these templates adhering to PFQ requirements and for its users.[/li][
                            
                            ][li][b]Do not distribute your code[/b] to anyone else or to the public.[/li][
                            
                            ][li][b]Do not change your templates[/b] outside of adding your custom text. Any changes you make reflect as my work.[
                            ][br][
                            ][i]I'm more than happy to add new features for you, ensuring your template adheres to PFQ rules and looks nice!![/i][/li][
                            
                            ][li][b]Do not remove the credit[/b] from the code templates.[
                            ][br][
                            ][i]You may, however, add to the credits if you'd like to include other artists there as well![/i][/li][
                            
                            ][li]Please provide [b]half of your payment[/b] upfront in order to get your spot in the queue![/li][
                            
                            ][li]Templates are completed in the [b]order I recieve them[/b]![/li][
                            
                            ][li]If you [b]order a bundle[/b], the items will be entered into the queue [b]individually[/b].[
                            ][br][
                            ][i]Eg. If you order a Journal and Forum Post templates, they will take up two slots on the queue, one after another.[/i][/li][
                            
                            ][li]Do keep in mind that the [b]template versions[/b] of your code may be [b]showcased in the Examples section[/b] for others to see.[/li][
                        
                        ][/ol][
                        
